[Anthrax is enzootic in Tamil Nadu, not least because of the contaminated waste water downstream from slaughter houses and hide processing plants. In the past 5 years it reported 8 mixed cattle and small ruminant outbreaks in 2006, 2007 (12), 2009 (11), 2010 (4), and in 2011 (10). For good or ill they rarely report human cases these years, but this might just be a bureaucratic oversight.

For a map of India showing Tamil Nadu, visit:
http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/india_pol01.jpg
For Theni, go to:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theni_district
For Cumbum, go to:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cumbum,_Tamil_Nadu - Mod.MHJ]
